article.headline: Murray St. 80, Ind.-South Bend 62
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Danero Thomas scored 16 points as Murray State beat Indiana-South Bend 80-62 on Tuesday night. Thomas also had nine rebounds for the Racers (9-7). Tyler Holloway was perfect from the floor, going 4-for-4 on 3-pointers, and scored 14 points, while Bruce Carter added 13 points. Qadr Owens scored 20 points for the Titans (13-8). Dewey Brown added 13 points, and Tyler Leighton had 11, hitting three 3-pointers. Murray State opened the game with a 20-7 run, and the Titans didn't get any closer than nine the rest of the way. The Racers led by as much as 45-22 after a 19-5 run to finish the first half.
